Subject: [PATCH 1/1] RDMA/nldev: Add checks for nla_nest_start() in
 fill_stat_counter_qps()
Git-commit: ea5ef136e215fdef35f14010bc51fcd6686e6922
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc1
References: git-fixes

As the nla_nest_start() may fail with NULL returned, the return value needs
to be checked.

Fixes: c4ffee7c9bdb ("RDMA/netlink: Implement counter dumpit calback")
Signed-off-by: Yuan Can <yuancan@huawei.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20221126043410.85632-1-yuancan@huawei.com
Signed-off-by: Leon Romanovsky <leon@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Nicolas Morey <nmorey@suse.com>
---
 drivers/infiniband/core/nldev.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/core/nldev.c b/drivers/infiniband/core/nldev.c
index 2be76a3fdd87..ca0ed7d14326 100644
--- a/drivers/infiniband/core/nldev.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/core/nldev.c
@@ -894,6 +894,8 @@ static int fill_stat_counter_qps(struct sk_buff *msg,
 	int ret = 0;
 
 	table_attr = nla_nest_start(msg, RDMA_NLDEV_ATTR_RES_QP);
+	if (!table_attr)
+		return -EMSGSIZE;
 
 	rt = &counter->device->res[RDMA_RESTRACK_QP];
 	xa_lock(&rt->xa);
